  </head>
  <body>

    <h1>💬 Words That Inspire</h1>
    <p>Great people throughout history have left behind powerful words. Here are some of our favourites.</p>

    <h2>Albert Einstein</h2>
    <p>Albert Einstein once said: <q>Imagination is more important than knowledge.</q></p>
    <blockquote cite="https://www.brainyquote.com/quotes/albert_einstein_148788">
      The measure of intelligence is the ability to change.
    </blockquote>

    <h2>Malala Yousafzai</h2>
    <p>Malala reminded the world that <q>one child, one teacher, one book, one pen can change the world.</q></p>
    <blockquote>
      I raise up my voice — not so that I can shout, but so that those without a voice can be heard.
    </blockquote>

    <h2>Nelson Mandela</h2>
    <p>Nelson Mandela believed that <q>education is the most powerful weapon which you can use to change the world.</q></p>
    <blockquote>
      It always seems impossible until it is done.
    </blockquote>

    <h2>Marie Curie</h2>
    <p>Marie Curie once said: <q>Nothing in life is to be feared, it is only to be understood.</q></p>
    <blockquote>
      I was taught that the way of progress was neither swift nor easy.
    </blockquote>

    <h2>Your Turn!</h2>
    <p>Which quote is your favourite? Add your own favourite quote below using a blockquote tag.</p>

  </body>
</html>
